The paper presents algorithms for partitioning paths and trees with weights on the vertices, which suggests that it belongs to the data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-categories. The use of parametric search also suggests that it could belong to the discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. Finally, the use of synthetic weighting and dual-pronged strategy suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
